   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="transcription">
            <p>
<lb corresp="#a1"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>s<surplus>ä</surplus></w><w>klāṅka-ṃ</w><w>kr<supplied>i</supplied></w><w>mā</w><w>kr<supplied>i</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#a2"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><supplied>ve</supplied>daśāsträntu</w><w>āklu</w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#a3"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>ñ<supplied>u</supplied>k</w><w>nu</w><w>säksäk</w><w>ś<gap reason="plain" unit="part"/></w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b1"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><supplied>tä</supplied>m</w><w>k<supplied>a</supplied>klyuṣurä<supplied>ṣ</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b2"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><supplied>ā</supplied>ly<supplied>a</supplied>käñcaṃ</w><w>wärtaṣiṃ</w><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b3"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><supplied>wra</supplied>saśśi</w><w>ārts<supplied>k</supplied>oṃ</w><w>ā</w><gap reason="lost"/></p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... he rode him/her, [if this is his/her] will or not ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... has taught the teachings of the vedas ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... but I ... sixty ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... having heard this ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... the ... of another forest ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... of the beings ... each day ...</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="remarks">The lower margin (recto) is preserved.</note><note corresp="#a1" type="philcomment"><hi>klāṅka-ṃ</hi>: cf. <bibl><title corresp="ref:carlingetal2009"/><citedRange>176b</citedRange></bibl>.</note><note corresp="#a2" type="philcomment">: cf. <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a97"/> b6 <hi>vedaśāstraṃ</hi>.</note><note corresp="#a3" type="philcomment"><hi>ñ(u)k nu</hi>: another possibility would be <hi>ñ (k)[a]knu</hi>. There is no vowel sign on top of the ‹ñ›, and there seems to be no ligature part below it, but a lower part ‹k› or ‹u› cannot be excluded.</note><note corresp="#b2" type="philcomment"><hi>(ā)ly(a)käñcaṃ</hi>: this variant is attested once more in <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a267"/> a1, against <hi>ālakäñcaṃ</hi> in <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a12"/> a3, <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a15"/> a6, <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a110"/> b5 (<bibl><title corresp="ref:siegetal1931"/><citedRange>193</citedRange></bibl>).</note></p>
         </div>
         <div type="bibliography">
            <p><label>Online access</label><bibl><title corresp="ref:idp0000"/><ref target="http://idp.bbaw.de/database/oo_loader.a4d?pm=THT 1144" type="external">THT 1144</ref></bibl><bibl><title corresp="ref:tht0000">TITUS</title><ref target="http://titus.fkidg1.uni-frankfurt.de/texte/tocharic/tht/11/1144.htm" type="external">THT 1144</ref></bibl>. </p>
